HEADWORD: Toothpick
<hw>Tooth"pick`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A pointed
instrument for clearing the teeth of substances lodged between
them.</def><-- esp., a slim sliver of wood, about two inches in length,
tapering to a point at both ends, and used for removing food particles
from between the teeth after a meal. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toothpicker</ent>⟦br⟧
